insert  into `thought_master`(`tid`,`tcontent`,`tauther`,`lastupdated`,`approved`,`deleted`,`placedOnFront`,`language`) values (46,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Would you sell both your eyes for a million dollars... or your two legs... or your hands... or your hearing? Add up what you have, and you\'ll find that you wouldn\'t sell it all for all the gold in the world.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:19:17',1,0,NULL,1),(47,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">You have it easily in your power to increase the sum total of this world\'s happiness now. How? By giving a few words of sincere appreciation to someone who is lonely or discouraged.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:19:36',1,0,0,1),(48,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">One of the most tragic things I know about human nature is that all of us tend to put off living. We are all dreaming of some magical rose garden over the horizon-instead of enjoying the roses blooming outside our windows today.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:19:54',1,0,NULL,1),(49,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Most of the important things in the world have been accomplished by people who have kept on trying when there seemed to be no hope at all.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:20:16',1,0,NULL,1),(50,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">It isn\'t what you have, or who you are,&nbsp;or where you are, or what you are doing&nbsp;that makes you happy or unhappy.&nbsp;It is what you think about.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:23:40',1,0,NULL,1),(51,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Inaction breeds doubt and fear. Action breeds confidence and courage. If you want to conquer fear, do not sit at home and think about it. Go out and get busy.</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dale Carnegie','2010-05-24 21:23:57',1,0,NULL,1),(52,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \"><a class=\"sqq\" href=\"http://thinkexist.com/quotation/life_has_meaning_only_in_the_struggle-triumph_or/150855.html\" style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; text-decoration: none; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#000000\">Life has meaning only in the struggle. Triumph or defeat is in the hands of the Gods. So let us celebrate the struggle!</font></a></span>','Swami Vivekananda','2010-05-26 23:06:29',1,0,NULL,1),(53,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 0, 51); font-weight: bold; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: small;\">Success is simple. Do what\'s right, the right way, at the right time</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n</font></span>','Unknown','2010-05-28 20:34:30',1,0,NULL,1),